[2] Cholera - Uganda: (Nebbi)
Date: Wed 12 Dec 2007
Source: AllAfrica. com and The Monitor (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200712121269.html>


The cholera epidemic has spread to 10 sub-counties infecting 331
people in Nebbi District. The District Surveillance Officer, Mr.
Benjamin Wanichan told reporters on Tuesday [11 Dec 2007] that 30
more cases were recorded. The total number of cases has risen from
301 to 331 within a week. Mr. Wanichan said new cases were reported
in the areas of Paidha, Kucwiny, Nyaravur and Erussi.

Mr. Wanichan attributed the disease escalation to contamination of
water sources. He noted that the task force and meetings with
sub-county leaders have been organized in order to step up
sensitisation on hygiene and sanitation.

[Byline: Warom Felix Okello]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

