[4] Cholera - Burundi: (Makamba)
Date: Mon 10 Dec 2007
Source: Agence France-Presse [edited]
<http://afp.google.com/article/ALeqM5io6BAPzAxt9yBDt9NCluY1rrmn3A>


A total of 2 people have died as a result of a fresh cholera outbreak
in southeastern Burundi, officials said Monday [10 Dec 2007].

"2 people died of cholera yesterday (9 Dec 2007) and another 57
people were hospitalized in the Nyanza-Lake health centre," 130
kilometers (80 miles) from Bujumbura, local official Epimene Batsinda
told AFP. He said that at least 152 people had been infected by the
disease since the outbreak was first reported on 1 Dec 2007.

Batsinda said that Nyanza-Lake town was prone to such epidemics since
the only form of sanitation and drinking water available to most of
its 54 000 residents is Lake Tanganyika.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The town mentioned is in the Makamba province, spelled Nyanza-Lac on
the map and can be seen at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/burundi.pdf>. - Mod.LL]

