[5] Cholera - Tanzania: (Dar es Salaam)
Date: Sat 8 Dec 2007
Source: IPP Media [edited]
<http://www.ippmedia.com/ipp/guardian/2007/12/08/103883.html>


At least 3 people are admitted to Buguruni Cholera Care Centre in Dar
es Salaam. Dar es Salaam Regional Commissioner Abbas Kandoro said
this on Wednesday [5 Dec 2007] when officiating at a regional
consultative meeting held at Temeke in the city.

He said among 37 patients who reported at Temeke hospital between 3
Oct 2007 and 1 Nov 2007, 3 were suffering from cholera. The rest of
the patients were found to be suffering from diarrhea. All of them
had since been treated and discharged.

He said since cholera had broken out again in the city people had to
ensure cleanliness of their environment including building better toilets.

Kandoro said it was a shame for a city such as Dar es Salaam to be
ravaged by cholera because the municipalities were putting a lot of
effort to ensure cleanliness. He said most cholera patients came from
Temeke municipality.

[Byline: Felister Peter]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Dar es Salaam, the capital, is located in northeastern Tanzania on
the Indian Ocean and it can be seen on a map of the country at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/tanzania.pdf>. - Mod. LL]

